<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8389557>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Aristolochia crocea. A. Branch. B. Perianth, inferior ovary, bract, and peduncle. C. Front view of the limb. D. Interior view of the utricle, which is composed of the gynostemium and the syrinx. E. Fruit. Based on L. J. González Almazán & C. Gallardo 238. Drawing by José Manuel Ramírez Amezcua." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8389557/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8389559>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. General morphology of Aristolochia crocea. A. Front view of the limb. B. Flowers. C. Lateral view of the perianth. D. Fruit. E. Habit. Photographs by Luis Javier González Almazán." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8389559/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8389563>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Distribution of Aristolochia crocea and morphologically closest species based on herbarium specimens." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8389563/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8389565>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Morphologically closest species to Aristolochia crocea. A–B. Aristolochia oaxacana (A. Paizanni-Guillén et al. 249 (IEB)). C. Aristolochia nelsonii. D. Aristolochia variifolia. E–F. Aristolochia versabilifolia (E. A. Paizanni-Guillén & J. M. Ramírez-Amezcua 485 (IEB) and F. A. Paizanni-Guillén et al. 254 (IEB)) Photographs by A. Paizanni Guillén. (A–B, E–F), Samuel Velásquez (C) and Saúl Borja (D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8389565/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

